author: Maxine Bernstein | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Oregon standoff defendants who dug trenches on refuge contend they were for self-defense
text: Prosecutors have charged Duane Ehmer and Jake Ryan with depredation of government property, and will have to prove they "wilfully'' broke the law by using a refuge excavator to dig two trenches on the federal property.
